hypothesis.hypothesis:
In cores/bench/rtl/mem_stage.sv's load-extract always_comb, replace
the variable barrel shifter:

    shifted   = dmem_rdata >> (in.alu_result[1:0] * 8);
    byte_val  = shifted[7:0];
    hword_val = shifted[15:0];

with explicit narrow muxes:

    // 4:1 on 8 bits — 1 LUT4 level per output bit (2-bit select
    // fits inside one LUT4 input)
    case (in.alu_result[1:0])
      2'b00: byte_val = dmem_rdata[7:0];
      2'b01: byte_val = dmem_rdata[15:8];
      2'b10: byte_val = dmem_rdata[23:16];
      2'b11: byte_val = dmem_rdata[31:24];
    endcase

    // 2:1 on 16 bits — 1 LUT4 level per output bit. Halfword loads
    // are half-aligned (bit 0 invariantly zero when not trapped),
    // so only bit 1 of the address selects the half.
    case (in.alu_result[1])
      1'b0: hword_val = dmem_rdata[15:0];
      1'b1: hword_val = dmem_rdata[31:16];
    endcase

The downstream load_data mux over (mem_width, mem_sext) stays
identical — it consumes byte_val and hword_val exactly as before.
The `shifted` intermediate wire is removed entirely (with its
verilator lint_off/on pragma), saving a 32-bit combinational
intermediate and the implicit 32-bit barrel shifter Yosys was
inferring behind it.

Expected mechanism for Fmax uplift: the dmem_rdata -> load_data ->
mem_wb_q.read_data flop arc loses ~1 LUT4 level on the bit-[15:0]
half (the full barrel's upper 16 bits were contributing to bits
[15:0] of `shifted` via the shift-by-16/24 arms), which is exactly
the late-arriving path r11s1 identified. Narrower extraction trees
also pack better in GW2A slices.

Misalign-trap semantics and byte-lane store mask (wdata_rep,
byte_mask) paths are untouched. RVFI mem_rdata tap still reports
the raw dmem word (mem_wb_q.mem_rdata <- dmem_rdata unchanged).
Every retirement's rd_wdata via the mem_to_reg WB mux is bit-exact
identical to the current behavior for every (dmem_rdata, addr,
width, sext) input combination.

Formal impact: zero. The load-extract value for any retiring LOAD
is functionally identical, so riscv-formal's insn_lb/lh/lw/lbu/lhu
checks see the same rd_wdata as before. No new pipeline state, no
RVFI wiring changes, no new hazard logic, no new ctrl bits.
